                <head>459. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>In conformity with <gloss target="#t_UN1">U.N</gloss>. General Assembly
                    Resolution 1348 (XIII), the Ad Hoc Committee on the Peaceful Uses of Outer Space
                    met in New York May 6–June 25. Although five designated members, Czechoslovakia,
                    India, Poland, the Soviet Union, and the United Arab Republic, declined to
                    participate, the committee established legal and technical committees of the
                    whole to consider various aspects of the use of outer space. The United States
                    was represented by Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_BLE1">Loftus Becker</persName> (Legal Committee), and
                        <persName corresp="#p_DHL1">Hugh L. Dryden</persName> (Technical Committee).
                    For text of the report of the committee to the 14th session of the United
                    Nations General Assembly, adopted June 25, see U.N. doc. <gloss target="#t_A1"
                        >A</gloss>4141.</p>
            </div>
